1
00:01:16,977 --> 00:01:18,847
[GROUP MARCHING NEARBY]

2
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:35,100
It's beautiful here.

3
00:02:36,423 --> 00:02:37,823
It was our aunt's.

4
00:02:38,392 --> 00:02:40,172
We used to come here as kids.

5
00:02:41,194 --> 00:02:43,333
The Order uses it now as a safe house.

6
00:02:45,198 --> 00:02:46,808
What's left of us, at least.

7
00:02:49,336 --> 00:02:52,906
Muggles think these keep evil away,
but they're wrong.

8
00:02:55,976 --> 00:02:57,616
I need to talk to the goblin.

9
00:03:09,723 --> 00:03:10,833
How are you?

10
00:03:13,060 --> 00:03:14,320
Alive.

11
00:03:19,599 --> 00:03:20,768
You probably don't remember--

12
00:03:21,101 --> 00:03:23,911
That I showed you to your vault
the first time you came to Gringotts?

13
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:27,621
Even amongst goblins you're famous,
Harry Potter.

14
00:03:31,745 --> 00:03:33,235
You buried the elf.

15
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:34,870
Yes.

16
00:03:35,182 --> 00:03:36,672
GRIPHOOK:
And brought me here.

17
00:03:39,319 --> 00:03:40,429
You are...

18
00:03:42,522 --> 00:03:44,542
..a very unusual wizard.

19
00:03:52,332 --> 00:03:54,322
How did you come by this sword?

20
00:03:59,106 --> 00:04:00,335
It's complicated.

21
00:04:02,576 --> 00:04:05,796
Why did Bellatrix Lestrange think it
should be in her vault at Gringotts?

22
00:04:07,614 --> 00:04:09,254
It's complicated.

23
00:04:12,786 --> 00:04:15,946
The sword presented itself to us
in a moment of need.

24
00:04:16,723 --> 00:04:18,093
We didn't steal it.

25
00:04:21,293 --> 00:04:24,313
There is a sword in Madam Lestrange's
vault identical to this one...

26
00:04:24,898 --> 00:04:26,328
.. but it is a fake.

27
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:28,159
It was placed there this summer.

28
00:04:28,535 --> 00:04:31,465
-And she never suspected it was a fake?
-The replica is very convincing.

29
00:04:32,038 --> 00:04:35,438
Only a goblin would recognize
that this is the true sword of Gryffindor.

30
00:04:36,076 --> 00:04:37,566
Who is the acquaintance?

31
00:04:37,944 --> 00:04:41,864
A Hogwarts professor.
As I understand it, he's now headmaster.

32
00:04:43,216 --> 00:04:44,116
Snape?

33
00:04:45,519 --> 00:04:47,659
He put a fake sword in Bellatrix's vault?

34
00:04:48,655 --> 00:04:49,554
Why?

35
00:04:49,856 --> 00:04:53,896
There are more than a few curious things
in the vaults at Gringotts.

36
00:04:55,262 --> 00:04:57,982
And in Madam Lestrange's vault as well?

37
00:05:01,101 --> 00:05:02,121
Perhaps.

38
00:05:04,638 --> 00:05:07,657
I need to get into Gringotts.
Into one of the vaults.

39
00:05:08,742 --> 00:05:09,762
This is impossible.

40
00:05:10,076 --> 00:05:13,506
Alone, yes. But with you, no.

41
00:05:19,085 --> 00:05:20,395
GRIPHOOK:
Why should I help you?

42
00:05:20,754 --> 00:05:23,154
I have gold. Lots of it.

43
00:05:23,657 --> 00:05:26,317
-I have no interest in gold.
HARRY: Then what?

44
00:05:31,932 --> 00:05:33,222
That.

45
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:35,566
That is my price.

46
00:05:49,149 --> 00:05:51,489
HERMIONE: Are you thinking
there's a Horcrux in Bellatrix's vault?

47
00:05:51,985 --> 00:05:54,175
HARRY: She was terrified when she
thought we'd been in there.

48
00:05:54,654 --> 00:05:56,294
She kept asking you
what else we'd taken.

49
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:59,270
I bet you there's a Horcrux in there,
another piece of his soul.

50
00:05:59,793 --> 00:06:02,373
Let's find it and kill it,
we're one step closer to killing him.

51
00:06:02,896 --> 00:06:04,476
RON:
And what happens when we find it?

52
00:06:04,865 --> 00:06:07,885
How are we supposed to destroy it
now you've given the sword to Griphook?

53
00:06:08,468 --> 00:06:10,248
HARRY:
I'm still working on that part.

54
00:06:12,839 --> 00:06:13,949
He's weak.

55
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:24,936
Yes?

56
00:06:26,853 --> 00:06:30,483
Mr. Ollivander, I need to ask you
a few questions.

57
00:06:31,157 --> 00:06:33,587
OLLIVANDER:
Anything, my boy, anything.

58
00:06:34,895 --> 00:06:37,145
HARRY:
Would you mind identifying this wand?

59
00:06:37,631 --> 00:06:39,941
We need to know if it's safe to use.

60
00:06:46,206 --> 00:06:47,756
Walnut.

61
00:06:48,875 --> 00:06:51,125
Dragon heartstring.

62
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:54,537
Twelve and three-quarter inches.

63
00:06:55,815 --> 00:06:57,425
Unyie--

64
00:06:59,753 --> 00:07:01,212
Unyielding.

65
00:07:02,522 --> 00:07:06,242
This belonged to Bellatrix Lestrange.

66
00:07:06,927 --> 00:07:09,387
Treat it carefully.

67
00:07:10,463 --> 00:07:11,573
And this?

68
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:16,771
Hawthorn.

69
00:07:18,305 --> 00:07:20,615
And unicorn hair.

70
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:25,207
Ten inches. Reasonably pliant.

71
00:07:29,316 --> 00:07:33,296
This was the wand of Draco Malfoy.

72
00:07:34,587 --> 00:07:36,777
Was? Is it not still?

73
00:07:37,257 --> 00:07:40,887
Well, perhaps not, if you won it from him.

74
00:07:43,763 --> 00:07:46,953
I sense its allegiance has changed.

75
00:07:52,072 --> 00:07:56,382
You talk about wands
as if they have feelings...

76
00:07:58,912 --> 00:08:00,022
.can think.

77
00:08:03,583 --> 00:08:07,483
The wand chooses the wizard, Mr. Potter.

78
00:08:08,588 --> 00:08:12,928
That much has always been clear
to those of us who have studied wandlore.

79
00:08:15,228 --> 00:08:17,748
And what do you know
about the Deathly Hallows?

80
00:08:23,103 --> 00:08:25,883
It is rumored there are three:

81
00:08:28,008 --> 00:08:29,847
The Elder Wand...

82
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:35,474
..the Cloak of Invisibility
to hide you from your enemies...

83
00:08:36,282 --> 00:08:41,412
..and the Resurrection Stone
to bring back loved ones from the dead.

84
00:08:42,288 --> 00:08:46,648
Together, they make one
the master of death.

85
00:08:47,427 --> 00:08:52,787
But few truly believe
that such objects exist.

86
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:55,160
HARRY:
Do you?

87
00:08:55,969 --> 00:08:57,839
Do you believe they exist, sir?

88
00:09:01,474 --> 00:09:07,424
I see no reason to put stock
into an old wivesâ€™ tale.

89
00:09:08,715 --> 00:09:09,765
You're lying.

90
00:09:11,184 --> 00:09:13,113
You know one exists.

91
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:15,163
You told him about it.

92
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:20,415
You told him about the Elder Wand
and where he could go looking for it.

93
00:09:24,564 --> 00:09:26,434
He tortured me.

94
00:09:29,302 --> 00:09:30,972
Besides...

95
00:09:32,172 --> 00:09:34,572
..l only conveyed rumors.

96
00:09:36,643 --> 00:09:38,013
There's....

97
00:09:39,412 --> 00:09:42,192
There's no telling whether he will find it.

98
00:09:45,618 --> 00:09:47,258
He has found it, sir.

99
00:09:53,393 --> 00:09:54,943
We'll let you rest.

100
00:09:57,730 --> 00:09:59,810
OLLIVANDER:
He's after you, Mr. Potter.

101
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:05,820
If it's true, what you say,
and he has the Elder Wand...

102
00:10:08,341 --> 00:10:09,831
.- I'm afraid...

103
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:13,190
.. you really don't stand a chance.

104
00:10:14,747 --> 00:10:17,877
Well, I suppose I'll have to kill him
before he finds me, then.

105
00:10:23,556 --> 00:10:25,486
RON:
Are you sure that's hers?

106
00:10:27,494 --> 00:10:28,864
Positive.

107
00:10:35,101 --> 00:10:36,501
Well?

108
00:10:37,804 --> 00:10:39,414
How do I look?

109
00:10:40,006 --> 00:10:41,496
RON:
Hideous.

110
00:10:42,408 --> 00:10:45,248
You can give that to Hermione to hold,
all right, Griphook?

111
00:11:05,498 --> 00:11:06,518
We're relying on you.

112
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:10,372
If you get us past the guards
and into the vault, the sword's yours.

113
00:11:23,416 --> 00:11:24,466
Madam Lestrange.

114
00:11:24,784 --> 00:11:26,334
HERMIONE:
Good morning.

115
00:11:27,854 --> 00:11:30,984
GRIPHOOK:
"Good morning"? "Good morning"?

116
00:11:31,591 --> 00:11:34,341
You're Bellatrix Lestrange,
not some dewy-eyed school girl.

117
00:11:34,894 --> 00:11:36,384
RON:
Hey. Easy.

118
00:11:36,763 --> 00:11:40,773
She gives us away, we might as well
use that sword to slit our own throats.

119
00:11:41,501 --> 00:11:43,141
Understand?

120
00:11:43,536 --> 00:11:46,606
No, he's right. l was being stupid.

121
00:11:47,307 --> 00:11:48,617
HARRY:
Okay.

122
00:11:49,042 --> 00:11:50,502
Let's do it.

123
00:12:41,461 --> 00:12:43,421
[PEN SCRATCHING PAPER]

124
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:50,181
[CLEARS THROAT]

125
00:12:55,275 --> 00:12:57,885
I wish to enter my vault.

126
00:13:01,447 --> 00:13:03,437
Identification?

127
00:13:06,819 --> 00:13:09,039
I hardly think that'll be necessary.

128
00:13:11,891 --> 00:13:13,501
Madam Lestrange.

129
00:13:18,931 --> 00:13:20,861
I don't like to be kept waiting.

130
00:13:21,901 --> 00:13:23,131
GRIPHOOK:
They know.

131
00:13:23,469 --> 00:13:25,369
They know she's an imposter.

132
00:13:28,474 --> 00:13:30,054
They've been warned.

133
00:13:38,318 --> 00:13:39,688
Harry?

134
00:13:40,586 --> 00:13:42,366
What do we do, Harry?

135
00:13:48,094 --> 00:13:51,554
Madam Lestrange,
would you mind presenting your wand?

136
00:13:52,932 --> 00:13:54,042
And why should I do that?

137
00:13:54,367 --> 00:13:59,257
It's the bank's policy. I'm sure you
understand given the current climate.

138
00:14:00,106 --> 00:14:02,856
No. I most certainly do not understand.

139
00:14:03,409 --> 00:14:06,779
I'm afraid I must insist.

140
00:14:12,485 --> 00:14:14,215
HARRY [WHISPERS]:
Imperio.

141
00:14:14,821 --> 00:14:17,131
[SNIFFS THEN SIGHS]

142
00:14:19,926 --> 00:14:23,616
Very well, Madam Lestrange.
If you will follow me.

143
00:15:00,299 --> 00:15:01,289
HARRY:
What is that, Griphook?

144
00:15:02,235 --> 00:15:04,135
[SQUEAKING AND GRINDING]

145
00:15:06,906 --> 00:15:08,075
Griphook.

146
00:15:15,748 --> 00:15:17,588
[ALL PANTING]

147
00:15:21,554 --> 00:15:22,843
[ALARM SCREECHING]

148
00:15:23,189 --> 00:15:25,059
[SCREAMING]

149
00:15:26,726 --> 00:15:29,356
HERMIONE:
Arresto momentum.

150
00:15:30,530 --> 00:15:32,079
[ALL GRUNT]

151
00:15:33,366 --> 00:15:34,566
HARRY:
Well done, Hermione.

152
00:15:34,901 --> 00:15:36,800
[ALARM CONTINUES SCREECHING
IN DISTANCE]

153
00:15:43,042 --> 00:15:44,682
Oh, no, you look like you again.

154
00:15:45,545 --> 00:15:48,915
The Thief's Downfall.
Washes away all enchantments.

155
00:15:49,549 --> 00:15:50,509
Can be deadly.

156
00:15:50,817 --> 00:15:52,247
You don't say.

157
00:15:52,618 --> 00:15:55,248
Just out of interest,
is there any other way out of here?

158
00:15:55,788 --> 00:15:57,248
No.

159
00:15:58,391 --> 00:16:01,851
What the devil are all you
doing down here?

160
00:16:02,495 --> 00:16:03,575
Thieves!

161
00:16:03,896 --> 00:16:05,886
-When you gave up the keys, you--
-Imperio.

162
00:16:06,332 --> 00:16:08,882
[SNIFFS THEN SIGHS]

163
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:12,886
[CREATURE ROARS NEARBY]

164
00:16:17,243 --> 00:16:19,173
That doesn't sound good.

165
00:16:21,247 --> 00:16:23,266
[GROWLING]

166
00:16:29,789 --> 00:16:31,019
RON:
Bloody hell.

167
00:16:31,357 --> 00:16:32,526
That's a Ukrainian lronbelly.

168
00:16:32,859 --> 00:16:34,199
Here.

169
00:16:38,831 --> 00:16:40,091
[ROARING]

170
00:16:44,971 --> 00:16:47,961
It's been trained to expect pain
when it hears the noise.

171
00:16:48,541 --> 00:16:49,881
HERMIONE:
That's barbaric.

172
00:17:19,771 --> 00:17:21,472
Lumos.

173
00:17:25,845 --> 00:17:27,185
Blimey.

174
00:17:34,487 --> 00:17:36,387
Accio Horcrux.

175
00:17:38,190 --> 00:17:39,940
You're not trying that one again,
are you?

176
00:17:40,359 --> 00:17:42,819
GRIPHOOK:
That kind of magic won't work in here.

177
00:17:47,366 --> 00:17:49,116
RON:
Is it in here, Harry?

178
00:17:50,202 --> 00:17:51,462
Can you feel anything?

179
00:17:59,579 --> 00:18:03,389
[HISSING AND WHISPERING FAINTLY]

180
00:18:08,421 --> 00:18:09,791
[HERMIONE GASPS]

181
00:18:13,359 --> 00:18:15,639
That's it. Up there.

182
00:18:19,465 --> 00:18:22,365
They've added the Gemino curse.
Everything you touch will multiply.

183
00:18:22,935 --> 00:18:24,225
Give me the sword.

184
00:18:42,421 --> 00:18:43,881
Stop moving.

185
00:19:06,479 --> 00:19:07,769
Got it.

186
00:19:10,583 --> 00:19:11,983
We had a deal, Griphook.

187
00:19:12,351 --> 00:19:13,551
The cup for the sword.

188
00:19:19,425 --> 00:19:23,815
I said I'd get you in.
I didn't say anything about getting you out.

189
00:19:46,018 --> 00:19:46,978
HARRY:
Griphook!

190
00:19:47,286 --> 00:19:48,746
GRIPHOOK: Thieves! Help!
-Griphook!

191
00:19:49,121 --> 00:19:50,731
Thieves!

192
00:19:51,957 --> 00:19:53,267
[BOGROD CHUCKLES]

193
00:19:53,626 --> 00:19:56,206
Foul little git.
Least we've still got Bogrod.

194
00:20:03,936 --> 00:20:05,275
That's unfortunate.

195
00:20:09,442 --> 00:20:11,372
HERMIONE: We can't just stand here.
Who's got an idea?

196
00:20:11,811 --> 00:20:13,150
You're the brilliant one.

197
00:20:13,512 --> 00:20:15,502
I've got something, but it's mad.

198
00:20:15,948 --> 00:20:17,118
Reducto.

199
00:20:30,196 --> 00:20:31,186
Well, come on, then.

200
00:20:33,966 --> 00:20:35,775
Relashio.

201
00:21:03,362 --> 00:21:05,002
[RUMBLING FAINTLY]

202
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:15,889
[ALL YELLING]

203
00:21:22,681 --> 00:21:24,381
GOBLIN:
He's moving! Aah!

204
00:21:46,572 --> 00:21:48,621
[PANTING]

205
00:21:51,210 --> 00:21:52,230
RON:
Now what?

206
00:21:52,545 --> 00:21:53,715
Reducto.

207
00:21:55,114 --> 00:21:56,344
Hold on.

208
00:22:06,058 --> 00:22:09,488
RON:
That was brilliant. Absolutely brilliant.

209
00:22:37,323 --> 00:22:38,843
HARRY:
We're dropping.

210
00:22:42,027 --> 00:22:44,017
RON: I say we jump.
-When?

211
00:22:44,463 --> 00:22:45,663
Now.

212
00:23:07,586 --> 00:23:08,486
[YELLS]

213
00:23:13,592 --> 00:23:14,702
[GASPING]

214
00:23:36,282 --> 00:23:37,742
[ALL PANTING]

215
00:23:40,252 --> 00:23:42,861
He knows. You-Know-Who.

216
00:23:43,389 --> 00:23:44,789
He knows we broke into Gringotts.

217
00:23:45,157 --> 00:23:47,966
He knows what we took
and he knows we're hunting Horcruxes.

218
00:23:48,527 --> 00:23:50,107
-How is it you know?
-l saw him.

219
00:23:50,496 --> 00:23:52,666
HERMIONE:
You let him in? Harry, you can't do that.

220
00:23:53,132 --> 00:23:56,262
Hermione, I can't always help it.
Well, maybe I can. I don't know.

221
00:23:56,869 --> 00:23:58,359
RON:
Never mind. What happened?

222
00:23:58,737 --> 00:24:00,317
Well, he's angry.

223
00:24:00,706 --> 00:24:02,075
And scared too.

224
00:24:02,441 --> 00:24:05,511
He knows if we find and destroy all
the Horcruxes we'll be able to kill him.

225
00:24:06,111 --> 00:24:09,331
l reckon he'll stop at nothing
to make sure we don't find the rest.

226
00:24:10,983 --> 00:24:12,973
There's more. One of them's at Hogwarts.

227
00:24:13,419 --> 00:24:14,909
HERMIONE:
What?

228
00:24:15,287 --> 00:24:17,627
-You saw it?
-l saw the castle and Rowena Ravenclaw.

229
00:24:18,123 --> 00:24:20,373
It must have to do with her.
We have to go there now.

230
00:24:20,859 --> 00:24:23,759
We can't do that. We've got to plan.
We've got to figure it out.

231
00:24:24,330 --> 00:24:27,080
Hermione, when have any of our plans
ever actually worked?

232
00:24:27,633 --> 00:24:29,743
We plan, we get there,
all hell breaks loose.

233
00:24:31,170 --> 00:24:32,280
He's right.

234
00:24:32,604 --> 00:24:36,324
One problem: Snape's headmaster now.
We can't just walk through the front door.

235
00:24:37,009 --> 00:24:41,199
Um, well, we'll go to Hogsmeade,
to Honeydukes.

236
00:24:41,947 --> 00:24:43,996
Take the secret passage in the cellar.

237
00:24:44,450 --> 00:24:47,410
It's-- There's something wrong with him.

238
00:24:47,987 --> 00:24:51,797
It's like, you know, in the past, I've always
been able to follow his thoughts.

239
00:24:52,491 --> 00:24:55,011
And now everything
just feels disconnected.

240
00:24:55,527 --> 00:24:56,667
Maybe it's the Horcruxes.

241
00:24:56,996 --> 00:24:58,746
Maybe he's growing weaker.
Maybe he's dying.

242
00:24:59,164 --> 00:25:01,914
No. No, it's more like he's wounded.

243
00:25:02,468 --> 00:25:04,928
If anything, he feels more dangerous.

244
00:25:09,641 --> 00:25:11,541
VOLDEMORT [IN PARSELTONGUE]:

245
00:25:29,595 --> 00:25:31,235
[NAGINI HISSES]

246
00:25:47,746 --> 00:25:49,796
[ALARM SCREECHING]

247
00:25:51,150 --> 00:25:52,380
[MEN SHOUTING NEARBY]

248
00:25:54,686 --> 00:25:56,386
MAN 1: They're here!
MAN 2: Search everywhere!

249
00:25:56,789 --> 00:25:58,839
MAN 1: Look down by the stables!
You two, come with me!

250
00:26:00,159 --> 00:26:01,469
MAN 3:
Any sign?

251
00:26:15,007 --> 00:26:16,757
[ALARM SCREECHING]

252
00:26:17,176 --> 00:26:18,076
MAN 4:
Potter!

253
00:26:31,457 --> 00:26:32,747
OLD MAN:
In here, Potter.

254
00:26:46,438 --> 00:26:48,168
Did you get a look at him?

255
00:26:48,574 --> 00:26:51,034
-For a second, I thought it was....
HERMIONE: I know. Dumbledore.

256
00:26:51,543 --> 00:26:53,243
[MEN CHATTERING NEARBY]

257
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:09,160
Harry?

258
00:27:11,330 --> 00:27:13,260
I can see you in this.

259
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:23,540
[DOOR OPENS]

260
00:27:26,211 --> 00:27:28,901
You bloody fools.
What were you thinking coming here?

261
00:27:29,448 --> 00:27:31,438
Have you any idea how dangerous it is?

262
00:27:31,884 --> 00:27:35,104
You're Aberforth, Dumbledore's brother.

263
00:27:36,121 --> 00:27:37,701
It's you who I've been seeing in here.

264
00:27:38,757 --> 00:27:40,157
You're the one who sent Dobby.

265
00:27:40,526 --> 00:27:41,666
Where have you left him?

266
00:27:42,261 --> 00:27:43,401
He's dead.

267
00:27:44,163 --> 00:27:45,913
Sorry to hear it. I liked that elf.

268
00:27:46,331 --> 00:27:48,910
Who gave that to you? The mirror?

269
00:27:49,701 --> 00:27:51,781
Mundungus Fletcher, about a year ago.

270
00:27:52,237 --> 00:27:55,107
-Dung had no right. It belonged to--
ABERFORTH: Sirius.

271
00:27:56,008 --> 00:27:57,648
Albus told me.

272
00:27:58,477 --> 00:28:02,167
He also told me you'd likely be hacked off
if you ever found out I had it...

273
00:28:02,848 --> 00:28:07,158
.. but ask yourself,
where would you be if I didn't?

274
00:28:10,722 --> 00:28:13,091
Do you hear from the others much?
From the Order?

275
00:28:13,592 --> 00:28:15,322
The Order's finished.

276
00:28:15,727 --> 00:28:16,927
You-Know-Who's won.

277
00:28:17,262 --> 00:28:20,252
Anyone who says otherwise
is kidding themselves.

278
00:28:20,832 --> 00:28:23,052
We need to get into Hogwarts, tonight.

279
00:28:23,802 --> 00:28:25,292
Dumbledore gave us a job to do.

280
00:28:25,671 --> 00:28:27,131
Did he now?

281
00:28:27,506 --> 00:28:29,646
Nice job? Easy?

282
00:28:30,576 --> 00:28:32,746
We've been hunting Horcruxes.

283
00:28:33,212 --> 00:28:36,232
We think the last one's inside the castle,
but we'll need help getting in.

284
00:28:36,815 --> 00:28:40,065
That's not a job my brother's given you.
It's a suicide mission.

285
00:28:40,686 --> 00:28:43,646
Do yourself a favor, boy, go home.
Live a little longer.

286
00:28:44,223 --> 00:28:48,322
-Dumbledore trusted me to see this through.
-What makes you think you can trust him?

287
00:28:49,294 --> 00:28:51,544
You think you can believe
anything my brother told you?

288
00:28:52,030 --> 00:28:55,340
In all the time you knew him,
did he ever mention my name?

289
00:28:56,768 --> 00:28:58,638
Did he ever mention hers?

290
00:28:59,071 --> 00:29:02,321
-Why should he--?
-Keep secrets? You tell me.

291
00:29:03,775 --> 00:29:06,845
-I trusted him.
-That's a boy's answer.

292
00:29:07,446 --> 00:29:10,166
A boy who goes chasing Horcruxes
on the word of a man...

293
00:29:10,716 --> 00:29:13,116
...who wouldn't even tell him where to start.
You're lying!

294
00:29:14,119 --> 00:29:17,458
Not just to me, that doesn't matter.
To yourself as well.

295
00:29:18,090 --> 00:29:19,870
That's what a fool does.

296
00:29:20,292 --> 00:29:23,722
You don't strike me as a fool,
Harry Potter.

297
00:29:24,363 --> 00:29:28,463
So I'll ask you again.
There must be a reason.

298
00:29:31,069 --> 00:29:33,969
I'm not interested in what happened
between you and your brother.

299
00:29:35,073 --> 00:29:37,063
I don't care that you've given up.

300
00:29:39,778 --> 00:29:42,088
I trusted the man I knew.

301
00:29:45,517 --> 00:29:48,237
And we need to get into
the castle tonight.

302
00:29:53,859 --> 00:29:55,999
You know what to do.

303
00:30:02,901 --> 00:30:04,601
HARRY:
Where have you sent her?

304
00:30:05,304 --> 00:30:08,434
You'll see soon enough.

305
00:30:15,080 --> 00:30:17,510
That's your sister, Ariana, isn't it?

306
00:30:18,684 --> 00:30:21,204
She died very young, didn't she?

307
00:30:22,487 --> 00:30:25,767
My brother sacrificed many things,
Mr. Potter...

308
00:30:26,391 --> 00:30:28,581
...on his journey to find power...

309
00:30:29,061 --> 00:30:31,051
.. including Ariana.

310
00:30:31,730 --> 00:30:34,280
And she was devoted to him.

311
00:30:35,233 --> 00:30:37,373
He gave her everything...

312
00:30:38,637 --> 00:30:40,157
... but time.

313
00:30:41,740 --> 00:30:43,850
HERMIONE:
Thank you, Mr. Dumbledore.

314
00:30:46,912 --> 00:30:48,722
[DOOR CLOSES]

315
00:30:50,982 --> 00:30:53,202
He did save our lives twice.

316
00:30:54,152 --> 00:30:56,052
Kept an eye on us in that mirror.

317
00:30:57,556 --> 00:31:00,246
[WHISPERS] That doesn't seem
like someone who's given up.

318
00:31:05,797 --> 00:31:07,637
She's coming back.

319
00:31:08,667 --> 00:31:10,506
RON:
Who's that with her?

320
00:31:18,043 --> 00:31:18,973
Neville.

321
00:31:19,277 --> 00:31:21,497
-Oh, you look--
-Like hell, I reckon.

322
00:31:21,980 --> 00:31:24,260
This is nothing. Seamus is worse.

323
00:31:25,183 --> 00:31:28,343
Hey, Ab, we've got a couple more
coming through.

324
00:31:29,955 --> 00:31:31,625
RON: Don't remember this
on the Marauder's Map.

325
00:31:32,023 --> 00:31:33,693
That's because it never existed till now.

326
00:31:34,092 --> 00:31:36,962
The seven secret passages were sealed off
before the start of the year.

327
00:31:37,529 --> 00:31:39,079
This is the only way in or out now.

328
00:31:39,464 --> 00:31:41,774
The grounds are crawling with
Death Eaters and Dementors.

329
00:31:42,267 --> 00:31:43,787
HERMIONE:
How bad is Snape as headmaster?

330
00:31:44,169 --> 00:31:46,749
Hardly ever see him.
It's the Carrows you need to watch out for.

331
00:31:47,272 --> 00:31:48,172
Carrows?

332
00:31:48,473 --> 00:31:50,643
Yeah. Brother and sister.
In charge of discipline.

333
00:31:51,109 --> 00:31:52,599
They like punishment, the Carrows.

334
00:31:52,978 --> 00:31:54,758
HERMIONE:
They did that to you? Why?

335
00:31:55,180 --> 00:31:58,400
NEVILLE: Today's Dark Arts lessons
had us practicing the Cruciatus Curse.

336
00:31:59,017 --> 00:32:00,687
On first-years.

337
00:32:01,086 --> 00:32:02,696
I refused.

338
00:32:03,722 --> 00:32:05,591
Hogwarts has changed.

339
00:32:18,737 --> 00:32:20,907
Let's have a bit of fun, shall we?

340
00:32:26,311 --> 00:32:28,890
Hey, listen up, you lot.
Brought you a surprise.

341
00:32:29,414 --> 00:32:33,014
Not more of Aberforth's cooking, I hope.
Be a surprise if we can digest it.

342
00:32:36,354 --> 00:32:37,314
Blimey.

343
00:32:37,622 --> 00:32:39,672
-Harry!
-Yeah!

344
00:32:52,637 --> 00:32:55,127
Get the word out to Remus and the others
that Harry's back.

345
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:57,540
Okay, let's not kill him before
You-Know-Who--

346
00:32:57,976 --> 00:32:59,316
River, D.A. calling. Do you read?

347
00:32:59,678 --> 00:33:02,338
We have a new weather report:
Lightning has struck.

348
00:33:02,881 --> 00:33:04,341
What's the plan, Harry?

349
00:33:09,421 --> 00:33:10,321
HARRY:
Okay.

350
00:33:11,423 --> 00:33:13,263
There's something we need to find.

351
00:33:13,692 --> 00:33:18,052
Something hidden here in the castle.
And it may help us defeat You-Know-Who.

352
00:33:18,830 --> 00:33:20,409
Right. What is it?

353
00:33:20,799 --> 00:33:21,819
We don't know.

354
00:33:23,935 --> 00:33:26,485
NEVILLE: Where is it?
HARRY: We don't know that either.

355
00:33:28,206 --> 00:33:31,045
-I realize it's not much to go on.
-That's nothing to go on.

356
00:33:31,610 --> 00:33:33,780
I think it has something to do
with Ravenclaw.

357
00:33:34,246 --> 00:33:38,346
Um, it'll be small, easily concealed.

358
00:33:39,784 --> 00:33:41,654
Anyone, any ideas?

359
00:33:43,255 --> 00:33:45,445
Well, there's Rowena Ravenclaw's
lost diadem.

360
00:33:45,924 --> 00:33:48,033
Oh, bloody hell. Here we go.

361
00:33:48,493 --> 00:33:50,303
LUNA:
Lost diadem of Ravenclaw?

362
00:33:51,229 --> 00:33:54,539
Hasn't anyone heard of it?
It's quite famous.

363
00:33:55,166 --> 00:33:58,126
Yes, but, Luna, it's lost,
for centuries now.

364
00:33:58,703 --> 00:34:01,163
There isn't a person alive today
who's seen it.

365
00:34:01,673 --> 00:34:03,603
Excuse me. Can someone tell me
what a bloody diadem is?

366
00:34:04,042 --> 00:34:06,442
It's a sort of crown.
You know, like a tiara.

367
00:34:07,312 --> 00:34:08,831
[RUMBLING]

368
00:34:10,047 --> 00:34:11,158
Harry.

369
00:34:12,583 --> 00:34:13,723
Hi there.

370
00:34:17,054 --> 00:34:19,745
Six months she hasn't seen me
and it's like I'm Frankie First-Year.

371
00:34:20,292 --> 00:34:21,842
-I'm her brother.
-Got lots of those.

372
00:34:22,226 --> 00:34:24,246
-There's only one Harry.
-Shut up, Seamus.

373
00:34:24,696 --> 00:34:26,005
What is it, Ginny?

374
00:34:26,364 --> 00:34:30,054
Snape knows. He knows that Harry
was spotted in Hogsmeade.

375
00:34:34,406 --> 00:34:36,686
[GROUP MARCHING]

376
00:35:09,808 --> 00:35:14,528
Many of you are surely wondering
why I have summoned you at this hour.

377
00:35:17,649 --> 00:35:20,959
It's come to my attention
that earlier this evening...

378
00:35:22,854 --> 00:35:24,843
...Harry Potter was sighted
in Hogsmeade.

379
00:35:25,290 --> 00:35:27,040
[MURMURING]

380
00:35:27,626 --> 00:35:29,026
Now...

381
00:35:29,394 --> 00:35:30,794
.. Should anyone...

382
00:35:32,664 --> 00:35:37,264
.. student or staff,
attempt to aid Mr. Potter...

383
00:35:39,037 --> 00:35:40,906
.. they will be punished...

384
00:35:41,339 --> 00:35:45,259
...in a manner consistent with
the severity of their transgression.

385
00:35:45,977 --> 00:35:47,937
Furthermore...

386
00:35:48,580 --> 00:35:52,680
..any person found to have knowledge
of these events...

387
00:35:54,586 --> 00:35:58,046
...who fails to come forward...

388
00:35:59,457 --> 00:36:03,467
...Will be treated as...

389
00:36:04,696 --> 00:36:07,506
. equally guilty.

390
00:36:10,201 --> 00:36:11,811
Now then...

391
00:36:15,507 --> 00:36:17,347
.. if anyone here...

392
00:36:18,076 --> 00:36:23,496
..has any knowledge of Mr. Potter's
movements this evening...

393
00:36:26,484 --> 00:36:29,884
..L invite them to step forward...

394
00:36:33,892 --> 00:36:35,381
. NOW.

395
00:36:46,137 --> 00:36:47,887
[MURMURING]

396
00:36:50,241 --> 00:36:53,671
It seems, despite your exhaustive
defensive strategies...

397
00:36:54,312 --> 00:36:56,652
. you still have a bit of a security problem,
headmaster.

398
00:37:00,485 --> 00:37:03,115
And I'm afraid it's quite extensive.

399
00:37:04,222 --> 00:37:06,062
How dare you stand where he stood?

400
00:37:07,926 --> 00:37:09,796
Tell them how it happened that night.

401
00:37:10,228 --> 00:37:14,208
Tell them how you looked him in the eye,
aman who trusted you, and killed him.

402
00:37:15,166 --> 00:37:16,596
Tell them.

403
00:37:34,953 --> 00:37:35,942
[WIZARDS GRUNT]

404
00:37:41,659 --> 00:37:42,559
McGONAGALL:
Coward!

405
00:37:45,630 --> 00:37:47,820
[STUDENTS CHEERING]

406
00:37:51,770 --> 00:37:53,940
VOLDEMORT:
Harry.

407
00:37:55,340 --> 00:37:56,390
McGONAGALL:
Potter?

408
00:38:06,317 --> 00:38:08,217
[RUMBLING]

409
00:38:13,591 --> 00:38:15,461
[GIRL 1 SCREAMING]

410
00:38:19,998 --> 00:38:21,898
[GIRL 2 SCREAMING]

411
00:38:26,371 --> 00:38:28,421
[GIRL 3 SCREAMING]

412
00:38:31,176 --> 00:38:36,066
VOLDEMORT:
! know that many of you will want to fight.

413
00:38:36,915 --> 00:38:41,335
Some of you may even think
that to fight is wise.

414
00:38:42,353 --> 00:38:45,043
But this is folly.

415
00:38:45,890 --> 00:38:48,379
Give me Harry Potter.

416
00:38:49,694 --> 00:38:53,354
Do this and none shall be harmed.

417
00:38:54,032 --> 00:38:59,332
Give me Harry Potter
and I shall leave Hogwarts untouched.

418
00:39:00,238 --> 00:39:02,817
Give me Harry Potter...

419
00:39:03,341 --> 00:39:06,801
..-and you will be rewarded.

420
00:39:07,445 --> 00:39:10,605
You have one hour.

421
00:39:20,792 --> 00:39:22,522
PANSY:
What are you waiting for?

422
00:39:22,927 --> 00:39:24,097
Someone grab him.

423
00:39:33,204 --> 00:39:34,874
FILCH:
Students out of bed.

424
00:39:35,907 --> 00:39:37,897
Students out of bed!

425
00:39:38,343 --> 00:39:39,712
Students in the corridor!

426
00:39:40,078 --> 00:39:43,067
They are supposed to be out of bed,
you blithering idiot.

427
00:39:44,849 --> 00:39:46,139
Oh.

428
00:39:46,885 --> 00:39:47,785
Sorry, ma'am.

429
00:39:48,086 --> 00:39:51,515
As it happens, Mr. Filch,
your arrival is most opportune.

430
00:39:52,156 --> 00:39:54,176
If you would, I would like you, please...

431
00:39:54,626 --> 00:39:58,576
...to lead Miss Parkinson and the rest
of Slytherin House from the hall.

432
00:39:59,297 --> 00:40:01,407
Exactly where is it
I'll be leading them to, ma'am?

433
00:40:01,866 --> 00:40:04,296
The dungeons would do.

434
00:40:04,802 --> 00:40:06,352
[CHEERING]

435
00:40:06,738 --> 00:40:09,107
FILCH:
Right. Come on. Come on.

436
00:40:09,607 --> 00:40:12,507
I presume you have a reason for returning,
Potter. What is it you need?

437
00:40:13,077 --> 00:40:15,327
Time, professor.
AS much as you can get me.

438
00:40:16,247 --> 00:40:19,377
Do what you have to do.
I'll secure the castle.

439
00:40:20,685 --> 00:40:22,085
Potter.

440
00:40:24,188 --> 00:40:25,768
It's good to see you.

441
00:40:26,925 --> 00:40:28,975
It's good to see you too, professor.

442
00:40:29,861 --> 00:40:31,821
Hold the fort, Neville.

443
00:40:32,363 --> 00:40:34,292
[STUDENTS CHATTERING]

444
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:37,150
GIRL:
Hurry up, come on!

445
00:40:43,574 --> 00:40:45,824
RON: Harry. Hermione and I
have been thinking.

446
00:40:46,311 --> 00:40:48,011
It doesn't matter if we find a Horcrux.

447
00:40:48,413 --> 00:40:50,283
-What do you mean?
-Unless we can destroy it.

448
00:40:50,715 --> 00:40:51,915
RON:
So we were thinking....

449
00:40:52,250 --> 00:40:54,440
Ron was thinking.
It was Ron's idea. It's brilliant.

450
00:40:54,919 --> 00:40:57,669
You destroyed Tom Riddle's diary
with a basilisk fang, right?

451
00:40:58,222 --> 00:41:00,122
Me and Hermione
know where we might find one.

452
00:41:00,558 --> 00:41:02,168
Okay.

453
00:41:02,560 --> 00:41:05,840
Okay, but take this. That way you can
find me when you get back.

454
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:08,274
-Where are you going?
-Ravenclaw common room.

455
00:41:08,700 --> 00:41:10,040
Gotta start somewhere.

456
00:41:16,307 --> 00:41:17,827
LUNA:
Harry.

457
00:41:18,209 --> 00:41:19,549
Harry!

458
00:41:19,911 --> 00:41:21,221
Let me get this straight.

459
00:41:21,579 --> 00:41:25,059
-You're giving us permission to do this?
-That is correct, Longbottom.

460
00:41:25,717 --> 00:41:26,977
To blow it up? Boom?

461
00:41:27,318 --> 00:41:28,628
Boom!

462
00:41:28,987 --> 00:41:31,977
Wicked. But how on earth
are we gonna do that?

463
00:41:32,557 --> 00:41:34,607
Why don't you confer with Mr. Finnigan?

464
00:41:35,059 --> 00:41:38,189
As I recall, he has a particular proclivity
for pyrotechnics.

465
00:41:38,796 --> 00:41:39,696
I can bring it down.

466
00:41:39,998 --> 00:41:42,078
That's the spirit. Now away you go.

467
00:41:43,234 --> 00:41:46,194
You do realize, of course, we can't keep out
You-Know-Who indefinitely.

468
00:41:46,771 --> 00:41:49,551
McGONAGALL: Well, that doesn't mean
we can't delay him.

469
00:41:50,608 --> 00:41:54,558
And his name is Voldemort, Filius.
You might as well use it.

470
00:41:55,279 --> 00:41:57,829
He's going to try to kill you either way.

471
00:42:00,451 --> 00:42:03,351
Piertotum Locomotor.

472
00:42:19,303 --> 00:42:20,883
Hogwarts is threatened.

473
00:42:21,272 --> 00:42:26,721
Man the boundaries. Protect us.
Do your duty to our school.

474
00:42:30,481 --> 00:42:33,761
I've always wanted to use that spell.

475
00:42:43,061 --> 00:42:45,671
Protego Maxima. Fianto Duri.
Repello Inimicum.

476
00:42:46,197 --> 00:42:50,267
Protego Maxima. Fianto Duri.
Repello Inimicum.

477
00:42:51,002 --> 00:42:55,192
Protego Maxima. Fianto Duri.
Repello Inimicum.

478
00:42:55,940 --> 00:42:57,400
Protego Maxima.

479
00:43:25,803 --> 00:43:29,673
-Harry, wait. I need to talk to you.
-I'm a bit preoccupied at the moment, Luna.

480
00:43:30,374 --> 00:43:32,683
You won't find anything
where you're going. You're wasting time.

481
00:43:33,177 --> 00:43:34,927
-Look, we'll talk later, okay, Luna?
-Harry.

482
00:43:35,346 --> 00:43:36,576
-Later.
-Harry Potter!

483
00:43:36,914 --> 00:43:38,614
You listen to me right now!

484
00:43:40,351 --> 00:43:43,041
Don't you remember what Cho said
about Rowena Ravenclaw's diadem?

485
00:43:43,888 --> 00:43:46,468
"There's not a person alive
who's seen it."

486
00:43:46,991 --> 00:43:51,121
It's obvious, isn't it?
We have to talk to someone who's dead.

487
00:44:02,073 --> 00:44:04,533
It's very impressive, isn't it?

488
00:44:20,224 --> 00:44:22,534
If you're to find her,
you'll find her down there.

489
00:44:23,027 --> 00:44:24,287
HARRY: Aren't you coming?
LUNA: No.

490
00:44:24,629 --> 00:44:26,819
I think it's best if you two talk alone.

491
00:44:27,298 --> 00:44:29,227
She's very shy.

492
00:44:56,027 --> 00:44:57,367
HARRY:
You're the Grey Lady...

493
00:44:58,329 --> 00:44:59,879
.. the Ghost of Ravenclaw Tower.

494
00:45:00,264 --> 00:45:01,784
I do not answer to that name.

495
00:45:02,166 --> 00:45:06,176
No, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
It's Helena, isn't it? Helena Ravenclaw.

496
00:45:06,904 --> 00:45:08,774
Rowena's daughter.

497
00:45:09,207 --> 00:45:10,987
Are you a friend of Luna's?

498
00:45:11,409 --> 00:45:13,109
HARRY:
Yes.

499
00:45:13,511 --> 00:45:15,681
And she thought you might be able
to help me.

500
00:45:17,882 --> 00:45:20,162
You seek my mother's diadem.

501
00:45:21,986 --> 00:45:23,475
Yes.

502
00:45:24,589 --> 00:45:25,519
That's right.

503
00:45:27,391 --> 00:45:31,491
Luna is kind,
unlike so many of the others.

504
00:45:32,230 --> 00:45:34,920
But she was wrong. I cannot help you.

505
00:45:39,937 --> 00:45:42,077
Wait. Please.

506
00:45:44,075 --> 00:45:45,855
l want to destroy it.

507
00:46:22,280 --> 00:46:23,740
[VOLDEMORT CHUCKLES]

508
00:46:24,115 --> 00:46:26,305
VOLDEMORT:
They never learn.

509
00:46:27,718 --> 00:46:29,528
Such a pity.

510
00:46:30,054 --> 00:46:32,984
But, my Lord...

511
00:46:33,557 --> 00:46:35,546
. shouldn't we wait for...?

512
00:46:35,993 --> 00:46:37,513
My Lord.

513
00:46:42,900 --> 00:46:44,190
Begin.

514
00:47:02,320 --> 00:47:04,510
[RUMBLING]

515
00:47:04,989 --> 00:47:07,039
That's what you want too,
isn't it, Helena?

516
00:47:12,897 --> 00:47:14,007
You want it destroyed.

517
00:47:14,332 --> 00:47:16,991
Another swore to destroy it
many years ago...

518
00:47:17,535 --> 00:47:20,055
..a Strange boy with a strange name.

519
00:47:20,571 --> 00:47:23,060
-Tom Riddle.
-But he lied.

520
00:47:23,574 --> 00:47:24,594
He's lied to many people.

521
00:47:24,909 --> 00:47:27,659
I know what he's done! I know who he is!

522
00:47:28,212 --> 00:47:30,762
He defiled it with dark magic!

523
00:47:46,097 --> 00:47:49,347
HARRY:
I can destroy it once and for all.

524
00:47:51,769 --> 00:47:54,379
But only if you tell me where he hid it.

525
00:47:56,707 --> 00:48:01,777
You do know where he hid it,
don't you, Helena?

526
00:48:04,014 --> 00:48:06,184
You just have to tell me.

527
00:48:07,985 --> 00:48:09,535
Please.

528
00:48:21,499 --> 00:48:23,519
Strange.

529
00:48:26,670 --> 00:48:29,390
You remind me of him a bit.

530
00:48:30,975 --> 00:48:32,085
It's here...

531
00:48:32,910 --> 00:48:36,660
..in the castle, in the place where
everything is hidden.

532
00:48:39,383 --> 00:48:40,613
If you have to ask...

533
00:48:40,951 --> 00:48:42,971
. you will never know.

534
00:48:44,255 --> 00:48:47,715
If you know, you need only ask.

535
00:48:49,360 --> 00:48:50,850
Thank you.

536
00:48:55,966 --> 00:48:57,336
[STUDENTS CLAMORING]

537
00:49:03,808 --> 00:49:07,588
Tell Professor McGonagall Remus and I
will handle this side of the castle.

538
00:49:08,946 --> 00:49:10,466
Yes, sir.

539
00:49:14,084 --> 00:49:16,834
SHACKLEBOLT: Hey, Dean, on second
thoughts, tell Professor McGonagall...

540
00:49:17,388 --> 00:49:19,848
..we might need one or two more wands
this side.

541
00:49:22,693 --> 00:49:25,323
REMUS: It is the quality of one's
convictions that determines success...

542
00:49:25,863 --> 00:49:27,413
.. not the number of followers.

543
00:49:27,798 --> 00:49:29,548
Who said that?

544
00:49:30,234 --> 00:49:31,604
Me.

545
00:49:36,540 --> 00:49:38,240
You okay, Freddie?

546
00:49:38,843 --> 00:49:40,103
Yeah.

547
00:49:41,745 --> 00:49:43,234
Me too.

548
00:49:51,822 --> 00:49:53,812
[SPEAKING IN PARSELTONGUE]

549
00:50:00,531 --> 00:50:03,721
Harry talks in his sleep.
Have you noticed?

550
00:50:05,035 --> 00:50:06,815
No, of course not.

551
00:50:33,230 --> 00:50:35,160
[YELLING AND SCREAMING
IN DISTANCE]

552
00:50:54,652 --> 00:50:56,082
Yeah?

553
00:50:56,453 --> 00:50:57,763
You and whose army?

554
00:51:18,142 --> 00:51:19,602
-You do it.
-I can't.

555
00:51:19,977 --> 00:51:21,817
Yes, you can.

556
00:51:49,640 --> 00:51:51,129
[YELLS]

557
00:51:52,543 --> 00:51:53,943
[GASPS]

558
00:52:33,384 --> 00:52:34,874
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

559
00:52:35,519 --> 00:52:36,828
[WAILS]

560
00:52:40,391 --> 00:52:42,171
[RUMBLING]

561
00:53:00,477 --> 00:53:01,817
[GRUNTS]

562
00:53:55,032 --> 00:53:57,082
[YELLING]

563
00:54:20,157 --> 00:54:21,587
GINNY:
Neville!

564
00:54:34,304 --> 00:54:35,884
[PANTING]

565
00:54:38,976 --> 00:54:40,646
That went well.

566
00:55:27,024 --> 00:55:30,594
McGONAGALL: Get inside!
This way, everyone. Take cover!

567
00:55:44,942 --> 00:55:46,282
[SCREAMING]

568
00:55:48,779 --> 00:55:50,359
HARRY:
Stupefy!

569
00:55:51,915 --> 00:55:53,255
Get your coat on!

570
00:55:53,617 --> 00:55:56,337
Ginny. Neville. Are you all right?

571
00:55:56,887 --> 00:56:00,867
Never better. I feel like I could spit fire.
You haven't seen Luna, have you?

572
00:56:01,592 --> 00:56:03,202
-Luna?
-I'm mad for her!

573
00:56:03,594 --> 00:56:07,374
I think it's about time I told her
since we'll probably both be dead by dawn.

574
00:56:11,869 --> 00:56:13,419
I know.

575
00:56:18,675 --> 00:56:20,135
[DRACO GRUNTS]

576
00:56:41,431 --> 00:56:43,711
Bloody hell. We'll never find it on this.

577
00:56:44,201 --> 00:56:46,541
-There he is, just there.
RON: Brilliant.

578
00:56:47,037 --> 00:56:49,906
He just vanished. Just now. I saw it.

579
00:56:50,474 --> 00:56:52,254
[RUMBLING]

580
00:56:53,477 --> 00:56:55,207
Maybe he's gone to
the Room of Requirement.

581
00:56:55,612 --> 00:56:58,652
It doesn't show up on the map, does it?
You said that last year.

582
00:56:59,249 --> 00:57:01,299
That's right. I-- I did.

583
00:57:01,752 --> 00:57:03,241
Let's go.

584
00:57:04,154 --> 00:57:05,674
Brilliant.

585
00:57:11,495 --> 00:57:12,955
DRACO:
Come on!

586
00:58:11,088 --> 00:58:13,258
[VOICES WHISPERING]

587
00:58:16,159 --> 00:58:18,149
[HIGH-PITCHED RINGING]

588
00:59:05,075 --> 00:59:06,245
DRACO:
Well, well.

589
00:59:07,377 --> 00:59:09,187
What brings you here, Potter?

590
00:59:10,280 --> 00:59:11,920
I could ask you the same.

591
00:59:12,749 --> 00:59:14,558
You have something of mine.

592
00:59:15,685 --> 00:59:17,025
I'd like it back.

593
00:59:17,387 --> 00:59:19,467
-What's wrong with the one you have?
DRACO: It's my mother's.

594
00:59:19,923 --> 00:59:23,323
It's powerful, but it's not the same.

595
00:59:23,960 --> 00:59:27,150
Doesn't quite understand me.

596
00:59:28,098 --> 00:59:29,388
Know what I mean?

597
00:59:30,167 --> 00:59:31,866
Why didn't you tell her?

598
00:59:33,770 --> 00:59:34,820
Bellatrix.

599
00:59:38,375 --> 00:59:40,075
You knew it was me.

600
00:59:41,044 --> 00:59:42,384
You didn't say anything.

601
00:59:42,746 --> 00:59:44,386
Come on, Draco.

602
00:59:44,781 --> 00:59:47,561
Don't be a prat. Do him.

603
00:59:48,752 --> 00:59:49,922
DRACO:
Easy.

604
00:59:51,488 --> 00:59:52,627
Expelliarmus.

605
00:59:52,956 --> 00:59:53,856
Avada Kedavra!

606
00:59:54,157 --> 00:59:55,057
Stupefy!

607
00:59:58,295 --> 00:59:59,345
[YELLS]

608
00:59:59,663 --> 01:00:02,323
RON:
That's my girlfriend, you numpties!

609
01:00:04,334 --> 01:00:06,234
[HARRY PANTING AND COUGHING]

610
01:00:10,807 --> 01:00:12,236
[CHATTERING]

611
01:00:12,609 --> 01:00:14,129
[SCREECHING]

612
01:00:24,287 --> 01:00:25,716
HARRY:
Got it.

613
01:00:32,696 --> 01:00:33,895
RON:
Run!

614
01:00:35,298 --> 01:00:36,348
Run!

615
01:00:36,833 --> 01:00:38,353
[RON SCREAMING]

616
01:00:40,537 --> 01:00:43,057
Goyle's setting the bloody place on fire!

617
01:01:05,028 --> 01:01:06,317
[ROARS]

618
01:01:44,634 --> 01:01:46,004
[SCREAMS]

619
01:01:50,407 --> 01:01:52,077
Come on! This way!

620
01:01:59,616 --> 01:02:01,366
We can't leave them.

621
01:02:01,785 --> 01:02:03,685
He's joking, right?

622
01:02:12,629 --> 01:02:15,118
If we die for them, Harry,
I'm gonna kill you.

623
01:02:31,248 --> 01:02:32,478
[GRUNTING]

624
01:02:38,154 --> 01:02:39,614
HERMIONE:
Harry!

625
01:02:55,138 --> 01:02:56,808
[HISSES]

626
01:02:58,575 --> 01:03:00,855
[PANTING AND GROANING]

627
01:03:26,269 --> 01:03:27,408
My Lord?

628
01:03:27,737 --> 01:03:29,957
Avada Kedavra!

629
01:03:36,613 --> 01:03:40,363
Come, Nagini. 1 need to keep you safe.

630
01:03:42,185 --> 01:03:43,915
[PANTING]

631
01:03:53,263 --> 01:03:54,873
HARRY:
It's the snake.

632
01:03:55,265 --> 01:03:58,424
She's the last one. It's the last Horcrux.

633
01:04:05,542 --> 01:04:07,652
RON:
Look inside him, Harry.

634
01:04:08,111 --> 01:04:11,421
Find out where he is.
If we find him, we can find the snake.

635
01:04:12,048 --> 01:04:13,917
Then we can end this.

636
01:04:41,878 --> 01:04:43,398
LUCIUS:
My Lord?

637
01:04:43,780 --> 01:04:47,180
Might it be less, uh....

638
01:04:48,418 --> 01:04:52,198
Might it not be more prudent
to call off this attack...

639
01:04:53,456 --> 01:04:55,506
..and simply seek the boy yourself?

640
01:04:55,959 --> 01:04:58,888
VOLDEMORT:
I do not need to seek the boy.

641
01:04:59,462 --> 01:05:03,332
Before the night is out, he will come to me.
Do you understand?

642
01:05:05,802 --> 01:05:07,552
Look at me.

643
01:05:07,971 --> 01:05:11,451
How can you live with yourself, Lucius?

644
01:05:12,108 --> 01:05:13,658
I don't know.

645
01:05:15,979 --> 01:05:18,198
Go and find Severus.

646
01:05:19,115 --> 01:05:20,924
Bring him to me.

647
01:05:29,192 --> 01:05:30,972
I know where he is.

648
01:05:40,904 --> 01:05:42,744
OLIVER:
Come on!

649
01:05:56,453 --> 01:05:57,942
[YELLS]

650
01:06:03,359 --> 01:06:05,169
[GRUNTING]

651
01:06:15,839 --> 01:06:17,509
[SPIDERS SQUEAKING]

652
01:06:23,046 --> 01:06:24,915
BOY:
Crucio!

653
01:06:30,920 --> 01:06:32,180
HERMIONE:
No!

654
01:07:18,501 --> 01:07:21,341
SNAPE: You have performed extraordinary
magic with this wand, my Lord...

655
01:07:21,905 --> 01:07:23,685
..in the last few hours alone.

656
01:07:24,107 --> 01:07:25,657
VOLDEMORT:
No.

657
01:07:26,342 --> 01:07:29,212
No, I am extraordinary...

658
01:07:29,779 --> 01:07:32,969
.. but the wand resists me.

659
01:07:33,583 --> 01:07:36,273
SNAPE:
There is no wand more powerful.

660
01:07:36,819 --> 01:07:39,279
Ollivander himself has said it.

661
01:07:39,789 --> 01:07:44,739
Tonight, when the boy comes,
it will not fail you. 1 am sure of it.

662
01:07:47,463 --> 01:07:49,953
It answers to you...

663
01:07:51,167 --> 01:07:53,217
..and you only.

664
01:07:54,237 --> 01:07:55,547
Does it?

665
01:07:58,741 --> 01:08:00,081
My Lord?

666
01:08:02,579 --> 01:08:06,389
The wand, does it truly answer to me?

667
01:08:08,685 --> 01:08:10,525
You're a clever man, Severus.

668
01:08:10,954 --> 01:08:12,624
Surely you must know.

669
01:08:14,557 --> 01:08:17,807
Where does its true loyalty lie?

670
01:08:18,761 --> 01:08:20,311
SNAPE:
With you...

671
01:08:21,029 --> 01:08:22,870
...of course, my Lord.

672
01:08:23,299 --> 01:08:24,349
VOLDEMORT:
The Elder Wand...

673
01:08:25,301 --> 01:08:30,401
.. cannot serve me properly
because I am not its true master.

674
01:08:32,207 --> 01:08:37,037
The Elder Wand belongs to the wizard
who killed its last owner.

675
01:08:43,620 --> 01:08:46,840
You killed Dumbledore, Severus.

676
01:08:48,157 --> 01:08:52,787
While you live,
the Elder Wand cannot truly be mine.

677
01:08:54,897 --> 01:08:58,176
You've been a good and faithful servant,
Severus...

678
01:08:59,135 --> 01:09:03,585
..but only I can live forever.

679
01:09:07,510 --> 01:09:08,410
My Lord--

680
01:09:11,747 --> 01:09:12,888
[THUDS]

681
01:09:14,550 --> 01:09:16,390
VOLDEMORT:
Nagini, kill.

682
01:09:25,194 --> 01:09:27,414
[SNAPE GASPING]

683
01:10:17,447 --> 01:10:19,177
SNAPE:
Take them.

684
01:10:20,583 --> 01:10:22,282
Take them.

685
01:10:23,352 --> 01:10:24,642
Please.

686
01:10:24,987 --> 01:10:28,237
Give me something. Quickly.
A flask, anything.

687
01:10:47,009 --> 01:10:48,299
SNAPE:
Take them to the Pensieve.

688
01:10:52,048 --> 01:10:53,777
Look at me.

689
01:10:59,756 --> 01:11:02,156
You have your mother's eyes.

690
01:11:10,600 --> 01:11:12,270
[SIGHS]

691
01:11:36,159 --> 01:11:39,289
VOLDEMORT:
You have fought valiantly...

692
01:11:41,130 --> 01:11:43,530
. but in vain.

693
01:11:47,170 --> 01:11:49,160
1 do not wish this.

694
01:11:49,605 --> 01:11:54,464
Every drop of magical blood spilled
is a terrible waste.

695
01:11:55,311 --> 01:11:59,500
] therefore command my forces fo retreat.

696
01:12:00,249 --> 01:12:05,108
In their absence,
dispose of your dead with dignity.

697
01:12:06,289 --> 01:12:11,589
Harry Potter, ! now speak directly to you.

698
01:12:12,495 --> 01:12:17,215
On this night, you have allowed
your friends to die for you...

699
01:12:18,034 --> 01:12:20,223
...father than face me yourself.

700
01:12:20,703 --> 01:12:23,833
There is no greater dishonor.

701
01:12:24,440 --> 01:12:28,799
Join me in the Forbidden Forest
and confront your fate.

702
01:12:30,646 --> 01:12:32,925
If you do not do this...

703
01:12:33,416 --> 01:12:39,306
.-f Shall kill every last man,
woman and child...

704
01:12:40,289 --> 01:12:44,299
..-who tries to conceal you from me.

705
01:13:04,413 --> 01:13:06,112
HERMIONE:
Where is everybody?

706
01:13:31,140 --> 01:13:32,040
Harry.

707
01:13:37,847 --> 01:13:40,277
SPROUT: Oh, come on.
What's the matter with you?

708
01:13:40,783 --> 01:13:42,213
TRELAWNEY:
Oh, she's passed.

709
01:13:44,220 --> 01:13:46,410
There, she's gone.

710
01:13:54,664 --> 01:13:56,563
[SOBBING]

711
01:15:55,451 --> 01:15:56,351
PETUNIA:
Freak!

712
01:15:56,652 --> 01:15:57,962
Come here.

713
01:15:58,320 --> 01:16:00,130
I'm gonna tell Mummy. You're a freak.

714
01:16:00,556 --> 01:16:02,696
You're a freak, Lily!

715
01:16:03,159 --> 01:16:04,558
Come here.

716
01:16:25,748 --> 01:16:28,647
SNAPE: She's jealous because
she's ordinary and you're special.

717
01:16:29,218 --> 01:16:31,438
LILY:
That's mean, Severus.

718
01:16:45,734 --> 01:16:47,344
[LILY LAUGHING]

719
01:16:54,577 --> 01:16:56,387
SORTING HAT:
Gryffindor!

720
01:16:56,812 --> 01:16:58,652
[STUDENTS APPLAUDING]

721
01:17:04,186 --> 01:17:06,766
-Hi. I'm James.
-Hi. I'm Lily.

722
01:17:11,694 --> 01:17:15,324
SNAPE:
Just like your father. Lazy. Arrogant.

723
01:17:15,998 --> 01:17:17,607
HARRY:
Don't say a word against my father.

724
01:17:24,140 --> 01:17:25,540
TRELAWNEY:
Blood shall be spilt...

725
01:17:25,908 --> 01:17:30,298
..and servant and master
shall be reunited once more.

726
01:17:31,080 --> 01:17:32,750
VOLDEMORT:
Severus.

727
01:17:34,049 --> 01:17:35,799
SNAPE:
No. Don't kill me.

728
01:17:36,218 --> 01:17:39,588
DUMBLEDORE:
The prophecy did not refer to a woman.

729
01:17:40,222 --> 01:17:42,212
It spoke of a boy born at the end of July.

730
01:17:42,658 --> 01:17:44,618
Yes, but he thinks it's her son.

731
01:17:45,494 --> 01:17:48,273
He intends to hunt them down now,
to kill them.

732
01:17:48,831 --> 01:17:52,781
Hide her. Hide them all. I beg you.

733
01:17:53,502 --> 01:17:56,222
DUMBLEDORE: What will you give me
in exchange, Severus?

734
01:17:58,340 --> 01:17:59,240
Anything.

735
01:17:59,542 --> 01:18:03,702
LILY:
Harry. Harry, you are so loved. So loved.

736
01:18:05,281 --> 01:18:07,621
Harry, Mama loves you.

737
01:18:08,117 --> 01:18:10,667
Dada loves you.

738
01:18:11,887 --> 01:18:13,786
Harry, be safe.

739
01:18:14,223 --> 01:18:15,123
Be strong.

740
01:18:15,424 --> 01:18:16,734
VOLDEMORT:
Avada Kedavra!

741
01:18:17,126 --> 01:18:18,676
[SCREAMS]

742
01:18:21,430 --> 01:18:25,350
SNAPE:
You said you would keep her safe.

743
01:18:26,068 --> 01:18:29,608
DUMBLEDORE: Lily and James put
their faith in the wrong person, Severus.

744
01:18:31,073 --> 01:18:32,883
Rather like you.

745
01:18:35,277 --> 01:18:36,567
The boy survives.

746
01:18:36,912 --> 01:18:38,902
He doesn't need protection.
The Dark Lord is gone.

747
01:18:39,348 --> 01:18:41,308
The Dark Lord will return.

748
01:18:41,750 --> 01:18:44,880
And when he does,
the boy will be in terrible danger.

749
01:18:46,522 --> 01:18:48,572
He has her eyes.

750
01:18:52,328 --> 01:18:55,108
If you truly loved her....

751
01:18:58,200 --> 01:19:01,570
No one can know.

752
01:19:02,204 --> 01:19:04,393
DUMBLEDORE: That ! should never reveal
the best of you, Severus?

753
01:19:04,873 --> 01:19:05,772
SNAPE:
Your word.

754
01:19:06,075 --> 01:19:08,625
DUMBLEDORE: When you risk your life
every day to protect the boy?

755
01:19:09,144 --> 01:19:12,274
SNAPE: He possesses no measurable talent,
his arrogance rivals that of his father...

756
01:19:12,881 --> 01:19:14,521
..and he seems to relish his fame.

757
01:19:14,917 --> 01:19:17,437
HARRY:
Don't say a word against my father.

758
01:19:17,953 --> 01:19:19,883
SNAPE:
James Potter?

759
01:19:20,322 --> 01:19:21,632
Lazy, arrogant.

760
01:19:21,991 --> 01:19:23,161
HARRY:
My father was a great man.

761
01:19:23,492 --> 01:19:25,162
Your father was a swine!

762
01:19:27,229 --> 01:19:28,689
SNAPE:
Drink the rest.

763
01:19:29,064 --> 01:19:32,604
It will contain the curse to your hand
for the time being.

764
01:19:33,269 --> 01:19:34,969
It will spread, Albus.

765
01:19:35,371 --> 01:19:36,861
DUMBLEDORE:
How long?

766
01:19:38,040 --> 01:19:40,210
SNAPE:
Maybe a year.

767
01:19:42,711 --> 01:19:43,731
Don't ignore me, Severus.

768
01:19:44,046 --> 01:19:45,356
DRACO:
Harmonia Nectere Passus.

769
01:19:45,714 --> 01:19:49,193
We both know Lord Voldemort
has ordered the Malfoy boy to murder me.

770
01:19:51,754 --> 01:19:55,474
But should he fail,
one should presume the Dark Lord...

771
01:19:56,158 --> 01:19:58,028
. Will turn to you.

772
01:20:01,030 --> 01:20:04,490
You must be the one to kill me, Severus.

773
01:20:05,134 --> 01:20:07,034
It is the only way.

774
01:20:08,270 --> 01:20:12,110
Only then will the Dark Lord
trust you completely.

775
01:20:12,808 --> 01:20:15,148
SNAPE:
Avada Kedavra.

776
01:20:18,714 --> 01:20:23,054
DUMBLEDORE: There will come a time
when Harry Potter must be told something.

777
01:20:25,220 --> 01:20:29,790
But you must wait until Voldemort
is at his most vulnerable.

778
01:20:30,592 --> 01:20:33,142
Must be told what?

779
01:20:33,662 --> 01:20:35,442
DUMBLEDORE:
On the night Lord Voldemort...

780
01:20:35,864 --> 01:20:38,674
..-went to Godric's Hollow to kill Harry...

781
01:20:40,069 --> 01:20:42,469
.-and Lily Potter cast herself
between them...

782
01:20:43,572 --> 01:20:45,272
. the curse rebounded.

783
01:20:47,309 --> 01:20:50,499
When that happened,
a part of Voldemort's soul...

784
01:20:51,113 --> 01:20:55,363
.. latched itself onto the only living thing
it could find:

785
01:20:56,118 --> 01:20:57,988
Harry himself.

786
01:20:59,588 --> 01:21:02,608
There's a reason Harry can speak
with snakes.

787
01:21:03,592 --> 01:21:06,081
There's a reason he can look into
Lord Voidemort's mind.

788
01:21:08,797 --> 01:21:14,126
A part of Voldemort lives inside him.

789
01:21:21,310 --> 01:21:23,890
So when the time comes...

790
01:21:25,147 --> 01:21:27,047
..the boy must die?

791
01:21:29,218 --> 01:21:30,998
Yes. Yes.

792
01:21:31,420 --> 01:21:33,410
He must die.

793
01:21:51,974 --> 01:21:56,254
You've kept him alive
so that he can die at the proper moment.

794
01:22:00,482 --> 01:22:03,642
You've been raising him
like a pig for slaughter.

795
01:22:04,253 --> 01:22:08,123
Don't tell me now that you've grown
to care for the boy?

796
01:22:13,162 --> 01:22:16,032
SNAPE:
Expecto Patronum.

797
01:22:27,342 --> 01:22:28,652
Lily.

798
01:22:32,114 --> 01:22:34,193
After all this time?

799
01:22:37,886 --> 01:22:39,756
Always.

800
01:22:45,160 --> 01:22:47,790
So when the time comes...

801
01:22:48,330 --> 01:22:50,960
...the boy must die?

802
01:22:51,500 --> 01:22:54,460
Yes. He must die.

803
01:22:55,037 --> 01:22:57,667
And Voldemort himself must do it.

804
01:22:58,474 --> 01:23:00,404
That is essential.

805
01:24:05,707 --> 01:24:06,637
HERMIONE:
Where've you been?

806
01:24:06,942 --> 01:24:09,722
-We thought you went to the forest.
-I'm going there now.

807
01:24:10,279 --> 01:24:12,889
RON:
Are you mad? No.

808
01:24:13,982 --> 01:24:16,172
You can't give yourself up to him.

809
01:24:19,821 --> 01:24:21,491
HERMIONE:
What is it, Harry?

810
01:24:23,258 --> 01:24:24,958
What is it you know?

811
01:24:27,963 --> 01:24:30,242
There's a reason I can hear them...

812
01:24:31,166 --> 01:24:32,246
... the Horcruxes.

813
01:24:34,903 --> 01:24:36,983
I think I've known for a while.

814
01:24:38,707 --> 01:24:40,697
And I think you have too.

815
01:24:43,946 --> 01:24:46,726
-I'll go with you.
-No, kill the snake.

816
01:24:47,849 --> 01:24:49,719
Kill the snake and then it's just him.

817
01:26:10,198 --> 01:26:11,978
I'm ready to die.

818
01:26:53,542 --> 01:26:55,682
The Resurrection Stone.

819
01:27:25,640 --> 01:27:28,630
You've been so brave, sweetheart.

820
01:27:33,115 --> 01:27:34,755
Why are you here?

821
01:27:35,784 --> 01:27:37,364
All of you?

822
01:27:39,955 --> 01:27:41,855
We never left.

823
01:27:50,999 --> 01:27:52,398
Does it--?

824
01:27:53,335 --> 01:27:54,385
Does it hurt?

825
01:27:55,570 --> 01:27:57,059
Dying?

826
01:27:58,206 --> 01:28:00,426
Quicker than falling asleep.

827
01:28:04,646 --> 01:28:06,666
You're nearly there, son.

828
01:28:07,115 --> 01:28:08,165
HARRY:
I'm sorry.

829
01:28:08,483 --> 01:28:11,553
I never wanted any of you to die for me.

830
01:28:13,588 --> 01:28:14,987
And, Remus, your son....

831
01:28:15,357 --> 01:28:19,107
Others will tell him
what his mother and father died for.

832
01:28:19,795 --> 01:28:22,835
One day, he'll understand.

833
01:28:35,010 --> 01:28:36,350
You'll stay with me?

834
01:28:38,113 --> 01:28:40,103
Until the end.

835
01:28:41,082 --> 01:28:42,812
And he won't be able to see you?

836
01:28:43,218 --> 01:28:44,678
SIRIUS:
No.

837
01:28:46,188 --> 01:28:48,468
We're here, you see.

838
01:29:03,338 --> 01:29:05,117
Stay close to me.

839
01:29:07,108 --> 01:29:09,008
Always.

840
01:29:24,025 --> 01:29:27,304
DEATH EATER:
No sign of him, my Lord.

841
01:29:43,211 --> 01:29:45,641
VOLDEMORT:
I thought he would come.

842
01:30:26,821 --> 01:30:30,041
Harry? No! What are you doing here?

843
01:30:30,659 --> 01:30:31,799
Quiet!

844
01:30:42,971 --> 01:30:44,960
Harry Potter.

845
01:30:48,343 --> 01:30:50,713
The Boy Who Lived.

846
01:30:55,283 --> 01:30:57,423
Come to die.

847
01:31:15,937 --> 01:31:17,427
Avada Kedavra!

848
01:32:00,849 --> 01:32:02,659
[MAN BREATHING FAINTLY]

849
01:32:14,329 --> 01:32:15,558
DUMBLEDORE:
You can't help.

850
01:32:16,664 --> 01:32:17,563
Harry...

851
01:32:18,299 --> 01:32:20,289
.. you wonderful boy.

852
01:32:21,069 --> 01:32:24,499
You brave, brave man.

853
01:32:26,941 --> 01:32:28,670
Let us walk.

854
01:32:36,384 --> 01:32:38,344
Professor, what is that?

855
01:32:41,322 --> 01:32:43,982
Something beyond either of our help.

856
01:32:47,228 --> 01:32:50,098
A part of Voldemort sent here to die.

857
01:32:50,865 --> 01:32:51,915
And exactly where are we?

858
01:32:53,334 --> 01:32:56,813
l was going to ask you that.
Where would you say that we are?

859
01:32:57,472 --> 01:32:58,992
Well...

860
01:32:59,374 --> 01:33:01,654
.. it looks like King's Cross station.

861
01:33:02,343 --> 01:33:04,363
Only cleaner.

862
01:33:04,813 --> 01:33:06,773
And without all the trains.

863
01:33:07,582 --> 01:33:09,982
King's Cross, is that right?

864
01:33:10,685 --> 01:33:13,815
This is, as they say, your party.

865
01:33:15,423 --> 01:33:18,053
l expect you now realize
that you and Voldemort...

866
01:33:18,593 --> 01:33:21,083
..have been connected by something
other than fate...

867
01:33:21,596 --> 01:33:24,255
... Since that night in Godric's Hollow
all those years ago.

868
01:33:24,799 --> 01:33:26,319
So it's true then, sir?

869
01:33:26,701 --> 01:33:29,311
A part of him lives within me, doesn't it?

870
01:33:30,004 --> 01:33:30,904
Did.

871
01:33:31,206 --> 01:33:35,426
It was just destroyed many moments ago
by none other than Voldemort himself.

872
01:33:37,078 --> 01:33:41,208
You were the Horcrux
he never meant to make, Harry.

873
01:33:54,329 --> 01:33:55,669
I have to go back, haven't I?

874
01:33:56,030 --> 01:33:57,700
Oh. That's up to you.

875
01:33:58,099 --> 01:33:59,649
I have a choice?

876
01:34:00,034 --> 01:34:01,614
Oh, yes.

877
01:34:02,003 --> 01:34:04,492
We're in King's Cross, you say?

878
01:34:05,940 --> 01:34:10,160
I think, if you so desired,
you'd be able to board a train.

879
01:34:12,147 --> 01:34:13,317
And where would it take me?

880
01:34:13,648 --> 01:34:14,728
[DUMBLEDORE CHUCKLES]

881
01:34:15,049 --> 01:34:16,659
On.

882
01:34:19,320 --> 01:34:21,540
[TRAIN WHISTLE WAILS IN DISTANCE]

883
01:34:34,869 --> 01:34:36,709
Voldemort has the Elder Wand.

884
01:34:39,607 --> 01:34:40,507
True.

885
01:34:40,808 --> 01:34:43,268
-And the snake's still alive.
-Yes.

886
01:34:43,778 --> 01:34:46,028
And I've nothing to kill it with.

887
01:34:46,881 --> 01:34:51,041
Help will always be given at Hogwarts,
Harry, to those who ask for it.

888
01:34:52,820 --> 01:34:56,070
I've always prized myself
on my ability to turn a phrase.

889
01:34:57,458 --> 01:35:00,208
Words are,
in my not so humble opinion...

890
01:35:00,762 --> 01:35:03,922
...our most inexhaustible
source of magic...

891
01:35:04,532 --> 01:35:08,342
.. capable of both inflicting injury
and remedying it.

892
01:35:09,504 --> 01:35:14,693
But I would, in this case,
amend my original statement to this:

893
01:35:18,213 --> 01:35:23,633
Help will always be given at Hogwarts
to those who deserve it.

894
01:35:30,225 --> 01:35:32,655
Do not pity the dead, Harry.

895
01:35:33,428 --> 01:35:35,208
Pity the living.

896
01:35:36,030 --> 01:35:40,309
And, above all,
all those who live without love.

897
01:35:41,869 --> 01:35:46,619
Professor, my mother's Patronus
was a doe, wasn't it?

898
01:35:48,343 --> 01:35:50,623
That's the same as Professor Snape's.

899
01:35:51,813 --> 01:35:53,653
It's curious, don't you think?

900
01:35:54,082 --> 01:35:58,442
Actually, if l think about it,
it doesn't seem curious at all.

901
01:36:00,755 --> 01:36:02,655
I'll be going now, Harry.

902
01:36:03,458 --> 01:36:04,628
Professor?

903
01:36:09,297 --> 01:36:11,196
Is this all real?

904
01:36:12,133 --> 01:36:13,742
Or is it just happening inside my head?

905
01:36:14,135 --> 01:36:17,235
Of course it's happening inside
your head, Harry.

906
01:36:17,839 --> 01:36:21,149
Why should that mean that it's not real?

907
01:36:27,181 --> 01:36:30,340
Professor? What should I do?

908
01:36:34,555 --> 01:36:36,105
Professor?

909
01:36:39,694 --> 01:36:40,834
BELLATRIX:
My Lord?

910
01:36:41,162 --> 01:36:43,032
My Lord, are you hurt? My Lord?

911
01:36:43,464 --> 01:36:44,894
I don't need your help.

912
01:36:45,266 --> 01:36:47,635
BELLATRIX:
No. Come.

913
01:36:56,678 --> 01:36:58,288
The boy.

914
01:36:58,680 --> 01:37:00,380
Is he dead?

915
01:37:14,696 --> 01:37:16,626
[WHISPERS]
Is he alive?

916
01:37:17,065 --> 01:37:18,995
Draco, is he alive?

917
01:37:45,927 --> 01:37:47,597
Dead.

918
01:38:45,853 --> 01:38:47,373
[THUDS]

919
01:39:14,615 --> 01:39:16,925
GINNY:
Who is that Hagrid's carrying?

920
01:39:17,919 --> 01:39:19,529
Neville, who is it?

921
01:39:20,421 --> 01:39:22,611
VOLDEMORT:
Harry Potter...

922
01:39:24,058 --> 01:39:25,368
. 1s dead.

923
01:39:25,726 --> 01:39:27,096
No! No!

924
01:39:27,462 --> 01:39:28,662
VOLDEMORT:
Silence.

925
01:39:32,633 --> 01:39:34,383
Stupid girl.

926
01:39:35,770 --> 01:39:38,790
Harry Potter is dead.

927
01:39:39,373 --> 01:39:43,883
From this day forth, you put your faith...

928
01:39:44,679 --> 01:39:45,609
.
. IN me,

929
01:39:56,224 --> 01:39:58,274
Harry Potter is dead!

930
01:39:58,726 --> 01:40:00,396
[ALL LAUGH]

931
01:40:03,397 --> 01:40:06,437
And now is the time to declare yourself.

932
01:40:08,436 --> 01:40:10,835
Come forward and join us.

933
01:40:13,107 --> 01:40:14,597
Or die.

934
01:40:20,348 --> 01:40:21,248
LUCIUS:
Draco.

935
01:40:27,054 --> 01:40:28,694
Draco.

936
01:40:31,826 --> 01:40:33,496
NARCISSA:
Draco...

937
01:40:36,564 --> 01:40:38,234
..come.

938
01:40:49,443 --> 01:40:52,463
VOLDEMORT:
Ah. Well done, Draco.

939
01:40:53,681 --> 01:40:55,321
Well done.

940
01:41:18,105 --> 01:41:20,535
Well, [ must say I'd hoped for better.

941
01:41:21,042 --> 01:41:23,232
[VOLDEMORT'S FOLLOWERS LAUGH]

942
01:41:25,279 --> 01:41:27,829
And who might you be, young man?

943
01:41:29,450 --> 01:41:31,150
Neville Longbottom.

944
01:41:31,552 --> 01:41:33,102
[VOLDEMORT'S FOLLOWERS
LAUGHING]

945
01:41:36,691 --> 01:41:39,941
Well, Neville, I'm sure we can
find a place for you in our ranks.

946
01:41:40,561 --> 01:41:42,521
I'd like to say something.

947
01:41:48,936 --> 01:41:54,005
Well, Neville, I'm sure we'd all be fascinated
to hear what you have to say.

948
01:41:57,712 --> 01:41:59,902
-It doesn't matter Harry's gone.
-Stand down, Neville.

949
01:42:00,381 --> 01:42:02,661
People die every day.

950
01:42:04,652 --> 01:42:08,222
Friends, family.

951
01:42:10,758 --> 01:42:12,128
Yeah.

952
01:42:13,761 --> 01:42:15,661
We lost Harry tonight.

953
01:42:17,465 --> 01:42:21,415
But he's still with us, in here.

954
01:42:22,970 --> 01:42:24,670
So's Fred...

955
01:42:25,906 --> 01:42:27,456
..and Remus.

956
01:42:28,776 --> 01:42:29,946
Tonks.

957
01:42:31,445 --> 01:42:33,115
All of them.

958
01:42:34,515 --> 01:42:36,505
They didn't die in vain.

959
01:42:41,922 --> 01:42:42,852
But you will.

960
01:42:43,157 --> 01:42:45,237
-Because you're wrong.
-Ha-ha-ha.

961
01:42:45,693 --> 01:42:48,323
Harry's heart did beat for us.
For all of us.

962
01:42:48,863 --> 01:42:50,263
This is not over!

963
01:42:52,233 --> 01:42:53,693
[HARRY GRUNTS]

964
01:42:54,568 --> 01:42:56,178
Confringo!

965
01:43:00,174 --> 01:43:01,464
[YELLING]

966
01:43:04,712 --> 01:43:06,082
BELLATRIX:
No! No, come back!

967
01:43:06,447 --> 01:43:09,907
Lucius! Come back! Come back and fight!

968
01:43:10,551 --> 01:43:12,361
Come back!

969
01:43:17,658 --> 01:43:20,438
I'll lure him into the castle.
We have to kill the snake.

970
01:43:20,995 --> 01:43:22,665
HERMIONE: You'll need this.
ARTHUR: Neville!

971
01:43:40,181 --> 01:43:41,611
[HISSING NEARBY]

972
01:43:51,225 --> 01:43:52,625
[WHOOSH]

973
01:44:49,550 --> 01:44:50,480
[YELLS]

974
01:46:09,663 --> 01:46:10,562
[HISSES]

975
01:46:13,200 --> 01:46:14,750
[CHUCKLES]

976
01:46:16,437 --> 01:46:18,657
Not my daughter, you bitch.

977
01:46:19,139 --> 01:46:20,399
[LAUGHS]

978
01:46:43,430 --> 01:46:44,830
[VOLDEMORT YELLS]

979
01:46:52,439 --> 01:46:53,609
HARRY:
You were right...

980
01:46:55,542 --> 01:46:57,592
..when you told Snape
that wand was failing you.

981
01:46:58,045 --> 01:46:59,505
It will always fail you.

982
01:47:01,015 --> 01:47:02,385
VOLDEMORT:
I killed Snape.

983
01:47:02,750 --> 01:47:04,620
But what if the wand
never belonged to Snape?

984
01:47:05,052 --> 01:47:07,572
What if its allegiance was always
to someone else?

985
01:47:08,088 --> 01:47:10,898
Come on, Tom.
Let's finish this the way we started it.

986
01:47:11,759 --> 01:47:12,659
Together.

987
01:47:15,529 --> 01:47:17,399
[BOTH YELLING]

988
01:48:40,914 --> 01:48:42,754
[YELLS]

989
01:50:18,479 --> 01:50:20,409
[STUDENTS CHATTERING]

990
01:50:47,274 --> 01:50:49,024
-Ha, ha.
-l always figured he would be a big fellow.

991
01:50:49,443 --> 01:50:53,253
I couldn't find my wand.
I haven't lost my wand in my entire life.

992
01:50:53,947 --> 01:50:55,697
It was lost in the folds of my gowns.

993
01:50:56,116 --> 01:50:58,576
I managed to find it
and I dispatched a few of them....

994
01:50:59,086 --> 01:51:00,166
HAGRID:
Harry.

995
01:51:00,487 --> 01:51:01,857
[HAGRID CHUCKLES]

996
01:52:00,781 --> 01:52:04,031
HERMIONE: Why didn't it work for him,
the Elder Wand?

997
01:52:05,452 --> 01:52:07,152
It answered to somebody else.

998
01:52:08,355 --> 01:52:10,785
When he killed Snape,
he thought the wand would become his.

999
01:52:11,291 --> 01:52:14,951
But the thing is,
the wand never belonged to Snape.

1000
01:52:15,629 --> 01:52:19,579
It was Draco who disarmed Dumbledore
that night in the astronomy tower.

1001
01:52:20,300 --> 01:52:23,840
From that moment on,
the wand answered to him.

1002
01:52:25,205 --> 01:52:26,815
Until...

1003
01:52:27,207 --> 01:52:31,217
..the other night
when I disarmed Draco at Malfoy Manor.

1004
01:52:31,945 --> 01:52:33,815
So that means....

1005
01:52:35,616 --> 01:52:37,166
It's mine.

1006
01:52:39,519 --> 01:52:40,629
RON:
What should we do with it?

1007
01:52:41,221 --> 01:52:42,771
We?

1008
01:52:43,390 --> 01:52:47,110
I'm just saying, that's the Elder Wand,
the most powerful wand in the world.

1009
01:52:47,794 --> 01:52:51,254
With that, we'd be invincible.

1010
01:55:14,875 --> 01:55:16,335
Together.

1011
01:55:32,292 --> 01:55:33,522
[WOMEN LAUGH]

1012
01:55:33,860 --> 01:55:35,759
FATHER:
Look after each other.

1013
01:55:55,215 --> 01:55:56,765
-Bag?
-Yeah.

1014
